DESCRIPTION:Description    Capitol Hill Community Safety Roundtable Hosted 
	by GSBA Capitol Hill - Jen Carl is bringing together community members\, b
	usinesses\, and partner organizations for a collaborative roundtable focus
	ed on practical\, neighborhood-based safety solutions.  This in-person ses
	sion is designed as a roundtable \\+ brainstorming workshop. We'll break i
	nto small groups to discuss and problem-solve Capitol Hill's top safety co
	ncerns\, then bring key takeaways back together. Discussion Topics Traffic
	 Safety Police Capacity Community Capacity Property Crime Drugs & Alcohol 
	Event Details Date: Tuesday\, March 18 Time:4:00-5:30 PM Location: Seattle
	 Central College - Broadway Edison \\(BE\\) Building\, Room 1110/1111 1701
	 Broadway\, Seattle\, WA 98122 Get Directions Open to community members\, 
	business owners\, nonprofit partners\, and stakeholders who care about Cap
	itol Hill's safety and well-being.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/
	#/details/capitol-hill-community-safety-roundtable/18089680/2026-03-18T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
